        <abstract>
            <p>He does not accept Wallace’s definition of instinct because it excludes "inherited experience", i.e., "knowledge acquired by and transmitted through ancestors".</p>
            <p>House-flies do not seem to have an instinctive fear of trap-door spiders.</p>
            <p>Miss Forster gives him news of CD.</p>
        </abstract>
